cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for classification tasks using hyperspectral imaging data. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper focuses on image classification. The use of data augmentation strategies and radiometric normalization approaches also suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these are common techniques in the field. The application of the method to robotics applications suggests a possible fit with cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The use of limited training samples and the need for efficient data collection suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these are areas where efficient use of data is important.
